# .extractignore — Files excluded from upstream extraction
#
# These files live in product-led-spec-kit but must NOT ship to the
# public agentic-oriented-development-kit template repo.
#
# Works like .gitignore: one path per line, # for comments, blank lines ignored.
# Paths are relative to repo root. Supports exact paths and glob patterns (e.g., docs/FEATURE-*).
#
# NOTE: The extract manifest (scripts/extract.sh) is opt-in — only directories
# and files explicitly listed in MANIFEST_DIRS and MANIFEST_FILES get copied.
# This file is only needed for files that live INSIDE a copied directory but
# should not ship upstream. If a directory isn't in the manifest at all
# (e.g., docs/planning/), it's already excluded by default.

